<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-02T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-02T01:00:00-05:00" n="792" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19069.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-01T23:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1916, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Information from Chihuahua to-night confirmed recent battle at Satevo,
                            but is that Villa defeated the Carrancistas, the Carrancistas losing
                            about two hundred men. Villa drove the Carrancistas north. The
                            unconfirmed rumor is that Villa whipped them again at Santa Ysabel and
                            there seized a military train which he [is] said to have used as far as
                            San Andreas from which point he is said to have gone toward Santa Clara
                            Canyon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>